Wordsmith tells the story of Clay Washburn, a penny and a half a word pulp writer trying to make it from day to day in the Great Depression.¬†

Clay wants to write more ‚Äúimportant‚Äù things, but the fates never seem to let him do this.¬†

Told in a stark style that almost looks like line drawings and watercolor, Clay does not solve crimes or fight evil doers in his spare time, he just writes, and frankly spends a lot of time feeling sorry for himself for finding he has to work for the Pulps.¬†

The only action in the series comes from depictions of some of the stories he wrote. ¬† ¬†

description:
The Surrogates is a five-part limited series created by Robert Venditti and Brett Weldele and originally published in 2005 by Top Shelf Productions. It tells the story surrounding the events of a near-future world in which androids - surrogates - will have been placed in many kinds of social and professional functions, thus substituting human beings in society to a certain extent.

Detectives Harvey Greer and Pete Ford are the main characters, and it's their responsibility to deal with a techno-terrorist willing to force mankind living as it did before surrogates were created.
